nsproxy tests
====================

This directory contains integration tests for nsproxy. The integration test
suite consists of three core components:

1. Target Server
   A Python-based socket server running in the test process, acting as the 
   final destination for the network traffic. It handles bi-directional data
   transfer and listens on ports 39000 (TCP) or 39001 (UDP).

2. Proxy Servers
   The tests support both v2ray and 3proxy as proxy servers. Each proxy server
   runs on the host namespace and provides SOCKS5 and HTTP proxy services.
   nsproxy connects to this server to forward captured traffic.
   It listens on ports:
   - 31080: SOCKS5 No Auth
   - 31081: SOCKS5 Auth
   - 38080: HTTP No Auth
   - 38081: HTTP Auth

3. nc client (Application)
   A netcat instance launched by nsproxy. It runs inside a fresh network
   namespace. Any network requests it makes (except to loopback) are
   captured by nsproxy and forwarded through the proxy server to the target
   server.


REQUIREMENTS
----------

 - v2ray OR 3proxy (installed and in PATH, or both)
 - netcat (nc)
 - Python 3 with pytest


USAGE
----------

To run all tests:
  pytest -v tests/

To run only tests with 3proxy:
  pytest -v -k "3proxy" tests/

To run only tests with v2ray:
  pytest -v -k "v2ray" tests/

To run only normal tests (skip Valgrind):
  pytest -v -k "normal" tests/

To run only Valgrind tests:
  pytest -v -k "valgrind" tests/

To see detailed logs (including nsproxy verbose logs and Valgrind reports):
  pytest -v -s tests/

Note: nsproxy runs in verbose mode (`-vvv`) only when pytest is run with
verbose mode (`-v`). Without `-v`, nsproxy output is suppressed.

VALGRIND TESTING
----------------

The Valgrind test suite is integrated into the standard pytest flow via 
parameterization. It uses the following flags:
- `--leak-check=full`: Perform a full memory leak search.
- `--show-leak-kinds=all`: Show all types of leaks (definite, indirect, etc.).
- `--error-exitcode=100`: Fail the test if Valgrind detects any errors or leaks.
- `--trace-children=no`: Only profile nsproxy itself, not the applications it 
  launches.

Note: To run Valgrind tests correctly, the project should be compiled without 
Address Sanitizer (ASan). Use the following build command:
  cmake -S . -B build -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=RelWithDebInfo -DCMAKE_C_FLAGS="-g -O0 -fno-omit-frame-pointer"
  cmake --build build
